headline: Can France's right and center agree on a common presidential candidate?
description: While some supporters of President Emmanuel Macron have called for a joint primary with the right-wing Les Républicains, the main candidates have refused to take part, raising questions about whether their platforms are even compatible.

description: Catherine Pégard, 71, was the head of the Château de Versailles for more than 12 years. She will have to oversee several major projects, including the Louvre renovation project.

headline: 'The rebuilding of Iran's ballistic capabilities is more concerning than a rapid nuclear restart'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, researcher Nicole Grajewski analyzes the current state of Tehran's military capabilities eight months after the Israeli-American strikes in June 2025.

headline: 'The Epstein scandal is astonishing by the scale of the complicity and rape culture at the top of society'
description: The philosopher Marc Crépon, who specializes in the forms and effects of violence, analyzes the public response to the sex scandal in an interview with Le Monde. He warns against the risk of disregarding the suffering and trauma of the victims.

headline: How Paris is turning into 'Frollywood,' a refuge for American actors
description: Whether George Clooney, Matt Dillon or Kristen Stewart, France is attracting more and more actors from across the Atlantic. This trend speaks to both the Trump-era crisis and the decline of the Hollywood model.

description: Former French culture minister Jack Lang and his daughter Caroline Lang appear thousands of times in the most recently released documents. All evidence suggests that she had a much closer relationship with the sex offender than she now admits.

headline: 'The unnatural alliance between Trump and White evangelicals has cost them dearly, even if it allowed them to gain positions of power'
description: Historian Sébastien Fath discusses the history and dynamics of evangelical Protestant churches in an interview with Le Monde. Despite their current vibrancy, their growth is not inevitable, the researcher argues.

headline: Four years of war in Ukraine: Five photographers on assignment for Le Monde share their most striking images from 2025
description: Five photographers who covered the conflict in 2025 have each chosen an emblematic image of the conflict. Beyond the official figures and statements, these unique perspectives reveal the mark that this new year of war has left on them.
